Package arcade.core.util

Class Parameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.core.util.Parameters
  • public class Parameters
extends java.lang.Object
    Container for parameters and parameter distributions.

    Parameters objects contain a MiniBox of population parameters along with parameter distributions. Utility methods are provided to return parameters as specific types.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Parameters

        public Parameters​(MiniBox popParameters,
                  Parameters cellParameters,
                  ec.util.MersenneTwisterFast random)
        Creates a cell Parameters instance.

        Parameters with distributions are tagged as DISTRIBUTION in the population parameters dictionary. Each of these parameters are converted to a Distribution instance. If a parent cell parameters is passed, the parent parameter distributions are used to generate the Distribution instance instead.

        Parameters:
        popParameters - the cell population parameters
        cellParameters - the parent cell parameters
        random - the random number generator

      • compare

        public boolean compare​(Parameters parameters)
        Compares two Parameters instances.

        Instances are equal if (1) both parameters have the same population parameters and (2) both parameters have the same distributions. Note that distributions are the same if they have the same distribution parameters; the value pulled from each distribution is ignored.

        Parameters:
        parameters - the Parameters to compare to
        Returns:
        true if contents match, false otherwise
